{"PageNumber":19,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Classic cipher – Hill cipher","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":308},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":184},"RightBottom":{"X":1605,"Y":308},"RightTop":{"X":1605,"Y":184}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Hill cipher takes a block of m letters, each interpreted as a number from 0 to 25, and interprets this block as a vector of length m","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":546},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":423},"RightBottom":{"X":2523,"Y":546},"RightTop":{"X":2523,"Y":423}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Thus, if $m = 3$ and a block is the string \"CAT,\" then we would represent this","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":713},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":642},"RightBottom":{"X":2250,"Y":713},"RightTop":{"X":2250,"Y":642}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● block as the vector: $\\vec{x} = \\begin{bmatrix} 2 \\\\ 0 \\\\ 19 \\end{bmatrix}$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":966},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":713},"RightBottom":{"X":1055,"Y":966},"RightTop":{"X":1055,"Y":713}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The cipher uses an $m \\times m$ random matrix, $K$, as the key, provided that $K$ is invertible when we perform all arithmetic modulo 26","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":1083},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":960},"RightBottom":{"X":2653,"Y":1083},"RightTop":{"X":2653,"Y":960}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The ciphertext vector, $\\vec{c}$, for $\\vec{x}$, is determined by the matrix equation","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":1167},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":1096},"RightBottom":{"X":2086,"Y":1167},"RightTop":{"X":2086,"Y":1096}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● $\\vec{c} = K.\\vec{x},$ denotes matric multiplication with all arithmetic is done modulo 26.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":320,"Y":1235},"LeftTop":{"X":320,"Y":1170},"RightBottom":{"X":2184,"Y":1235},"RightTop":{"X":2184,"Y":1170}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"• The decryption is done this way: $\\vec{x} = K^{-1}$. $\\vec{c}$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":1319},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":1245},"RightBottom":{"X":1449,"Y":1319},"RightTop":{"X":1449,"Y":1245}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":8,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● This holds, because: $K^{-1}.\\vec{c} = K^{-1}(K.\\vec{x}) = (K^{-1}.K).\\vec{x} = \\vec{1}.\\vec{x} = \\vec{x}$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":211,"Y":1412},"LeftTop":{"X":211,"Y":1326},"RightBottom":{"X":2077,"Y":1412},"RightTop":{"X":2077,"Y":1326}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}